object: Choricarpia is a genus of trees comprising two species endemic to New South Wales and Queensland in Australia:Choricarpia leptopetala, Brown Myrtle or Brush TurpentineChoricarpia subargentea, Giant Ironwood or Ironwood Box↑
human_readable: Choricarpia is a genus of trees comprising two species endemic to New South Wales and Queensland in Australia: Choricarpia leptopetala, known as Brown Myrtle or Brush Turpentine, and Choricarpia subargentea, also known as Giant Ironwood or Ironwood Box.
